ZH: 今天下了课后，同学们一哄而散。
EN: After class today, the students all scattered.

ZH: 演出结束后，观众们一哄而散。
EN: After the performance, the audience dispersed.

ZH: 会议室里的人们一哄而散，纷纷回办公室去了。
EN: The people in the meeting room all scattered, heading back to their offices.

ZH: 他们一哄而散，各自找自己的朋友去了。
EN: They all scattered, each going to find their own friends.

ZH: 在火灾发生时，人们一哄而散，逃离现场。
EN: When the fire broke out, people scattered and fled the scene.

ZH: 餐厅突然起火，人们一哄而散，惊慌失措。
EN: The restaurant suddenly caught fire, and people scattered in panic.

ZH: 最后一声钟响，学生们一哄而散，开启暑假生活。
EN: With the final bell ringing, the students all scattered, beginning their summer vacation.

ZH: 当宣布取消活动时，观众们一哄而散，失望地离开了。
EN: When the event was announced to be canceled, the audience all scattered, leaving disappointed.

ZH: 警察突然赶来，抓获了歹徒，围观群众一哄而散。
EN: The police suddenly arrived and caught the criminal, causing the onlookers to scatter.

ZH: 在演唱会结束后，人群一哄而散，回家去了。
EN: After the concert ended, the crowd scattered and went home.

ZH: 一阵风吹来，树叶一哄而散，飘落在地上。
EN: A gust of wind blew, causing the leaves to scatter and fall to the ground.

ZH: 当天空突然下起大雨时，游客们一哄而散，躲避雨水。
EN: When it suddenly started pouring rain, the tourists all scattered to seek shelter.

ZH: 在音乐会结束后，观众们一哄而散，各自回家。
EN: After the concert ended, the audience scattered and went home.

ZH: 在火灾中逃生时，大家一哄而散，不约而同地向安全出口奔去。
EN: When evacuating during a fire, everyone scattered and instinctively ran towards the nearest exit.

ZH: 当警察出现时，骚乱群众一哄而散，不愿被逮捕。
EN: When the police arrived, the rioting crowd scattered, not wanting to be arrested.

ZH: 下课铃响起后，学生们一哄而散离开教室。
EN: After the bell rang, the students all scattered and left the classroom.

ZH: 在车祸发生时，路人们一哄而散，不敢靠近现场。
EN: When the car accident occurred, the passersby all scattered, afraid to approach the scene.

ZH: 风暴来临时，人们一哄而散，躲避狂风暴雨。
EN: When the storm hit, people scattered and sought shelter from the strong winds and rain.

ZH: 演唱会结束后，歌迷们一哄而散，不舍离去。
EN: After the concert ended, the fans scattered, reluctant to leave.

ZH: 参加游行示威的人们遇到警察时，一哄而散，避免冲突。
EN: The people participating in the protest scattered when they encountered the police, avoiding conflict.
